properties.Name: BeneficiaryRevocationStatus
properties.Description:
Beneficiaries are classified as to whether they can be changed after a policy is issued.

The terms used to indicate this are revocable beneficiary and irrevocable beneficiary.

REVOCABLE DESIGNATION
The beneficiary in a Life Insurance policy in which the owner reserves the right to revoke or change the beneficiary.

IRREVOCABLE DESIGNATION
A Beneficiary that cannot be chanted without his consent.

The insurance policy is effectively owned by both the policyholder and the beneficiary.
